
// This Hyperlambda code sends a SignalR message to users with the "root" role using the [sockets.signal] slot. The message contains JSON-formatted arguments, including a "message" indicating that a plugin was successfully installed and a "type" of "success". The [roles] slot specifies the target audience for the message.
sockets.signal:magic.backend.message
   roles:root
   args
      message:Plugin was successfully installed
      type:success
